Claude writes a self-contained bpy Python script that models a structure from scratch
I run it in Blender's scripting tab and screenshot the result
Claude reads the screenshot, corrects proportions, geometry, or detail, and rewrites the script
We repeat until the model looks right
Claude exports as GLB and I drop it into the Godot project to replace the billboard

